title._content: First Kangaroo rugby league team, England, 1908-09

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: The Kangaroos are Australia's national team in rugby league. Back row: W. Hardcastle, A. Dobbs, J. Devereaux, A. Morton, C. Hedley, S. Deane, F. Cheadle, L. Jones, R, Graves, A. Halloway. Second back row: W. Cann, D. Frawley, T. Anderson, W. Heidke, S. Pearce, P. Moir, A. Burdon, L. O’Malley, J. Abercrombie, W. Noble (secretary). Second front row: W. Bailey, J. Davis, J. Rosewell, D. Lutge (captain), J. J. Giltinan (manager), H. H. Messenger (vice-captain), A. Hennessy, A. Conlon. Front row: M. Bolewski, T. McCabe, A. Rosenfeldt, J. Fihelly (assistant manager), A. Butler, E. Courtney, A. Anlezark. Format: Photoprint Notes: From the Davis Sporting Collection II From the collections of the Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au Information about photographic collections of the State Library of New South Wales: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx Persistent url: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=52646
